CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772741481
OL,3,COwner of high street jewellers uses
OL,4,CVictorian baton to chase off armed
OL,5,Crobbers
OL,7,FWARNING FLASHING IMAGES
OL,9,FCharles Pringle was on the shop floor
OL,10,Fat the time. He said:
OL,12,F"I've got an old Victorian truncheon,
OL,13,Fa police truncheon.
OL,15,F"It's very hard but unfortunately very
OL,16,Fshort.
OL,18,F"Anyway I grabbed that and went to the
OL,19,Fdoor- one of them was dancing around
OL,20,Fwith a machete sort of fending me off.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772741481
OL,3,COwner of high street jewellers uses
OL,4,CVictorian baton to chase off armed
OL,5,Crobbers
OL,7,F"At this point all the neighbours,
OL,8,Fpeople in the pub opposite and the
OL,9,Frestaurant next door were either
OL,10,Ffilming it or trying to help in some
OL,11,Fway."
OL,13,FAs Charles chased the helmet-clad men
OL,14,Foff with a baton, other bystanders
OL,15,Ftried to hurl a sandwich board and
OL,16,Fdifferent objects at them.
OL,18,FCharles has worked at the shop for 43
OL,19,Fyears.
OL,21,FHe told ITV News London that:
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772741481
OL,3,COwner of high street jewellers uses
OL,4,CVictorian baton to chase off armed
OL,5,Crobbers
OL,7,F"It just makes me so angry. People
OL,8,Fwork hard to build a living and they
OL,9,Fcan take it away in a thrash.
OL,11,F"They don't want to go to work
OL,12,Fproperly, they think that they're owed
OL,13,Fa living.
OL,15,F"I don't like people getting away with
OL,16,Fit."
OL,18,FSam Parish was also working at the
OL,19,Fjewellers on the day of the robbery.
OL,20,FShe told ITV News that:
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772741481
OL,3,COwner of high street jewellers uses
OL,4,CVictorian baton to chase off armed
OL,5,Crobbers
OL,7,F"I immediately phoned the police. You
OL,8,Fcan't put into words really how
OL,9,Ffrightening it was."
OL,11,FShe continued, "I hear a motorbike now
OL,12,Fand it triggers me. It's just
OL,13,Fsomething you don't think you'll ever
OL,14,Fexperience."
OL,16,FThe watches that the men grabbed were
OL,17,Fpre-owned Rolexes worth thousands of
OL,18,Fpounds each.
OL,20,FHerts Police are appealing for
OL,21,Finformation.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
